The paper is about a neural information retrieval (IR) model that incorporates context information to improve search results. This topic falls under the sub-category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also uses natural language processing techniques such as disambiguation and pooling, which are relevant to the sub-categories of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel model architecture that combines multiple signals, which is relevant to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Computer Vision (cs.CV).
